      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and once hot, add the<strong> remaining bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until crispy</p><p>Once the bacon is crispy, add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> to the pot with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once softened, return the <strong>cooked waxy potatoes</strong> to the pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook for 2-3 min or until warmed through – these are your <strong>bacon lardon potatoes</strong></p>",
